sql:
SELECT event_id, attendance_status
FROM event_participation_logs
WHERE student_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- "stars" refer to participants in the event;
- "constellation of the event" refers to a specific event identified by `event_id`;
- "shining with their achievements" refers to the count of achievements associated with the participants.

- "shining stars" refers to students who have performed exceptionally well;
- "top ratings" indicate the highest feedback ratings given by participants;
- "at least one accolade" means the student has received at least one award or recognition.

- An achievement is defined as securing a position in an event (e.g., 1st Place, Runner Up);
- The cumulative count is calculated over all events a student has participated in;
- The results are ordered by student ID and the cumulative achievements to show a progression.

- '2023' refers to the year in which the events took place;
- 'threads of events' metaphorically refers to different types of events (e.g., Competitions, Workshops);
- 'woven together the fabric of student participation' metaphorically refers to the involvement of students in these events;
- 'drew into its fold' metaphorically refers to the number of unique students who participated in each event type.

- "Top achievement" refers to the achievement with the highest rank based on the description;
- "Threads" metaphorically represent the students and their achievements;
- "Tapestry" metaphorically represents the collection of all student achievements.

- 'team member' refers to a participant who is part of a team in the event;
- 'average position' is calculated as the mean of the positions secured by the team members;
- 'more than one member' implies that the team has at least two participants.
